despite particular challenges, have reaped peace after first sowing it.

00:15:49.259 --> 00:15:55.259
Now one particular challenge to gaining peace is problems within the family.

00:15:55.259 --> 00:16:03.259
Because of imperfection, it s not uncommon to have disagreements, even tension from time to time.

00:16:03.259 --> 00:16:07.259
And family members may hurt one another in various ways.

00:16:07.259 --> 00:16:10.259
And usually such offenses are minor.

00:16:10.259 --> 00:16:13.259
And peace can quickly be sown and reaped.

00:16:13.259 --> 00:16:18.600
But what if the offense is more serious?

00:16:18.600 --> 00:16:24.600
A family member says or does something that hurts us deeply.

00:16:24.600 --> 00:16:32.600
Well, even then, it still may be possible to sow and reap peace.

00:16:32.600 --> 00:16:38.600
We can prove this by considering the Bible account of Joseph and his brothers.

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:40.600
And we are familiar with the story.

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:44.600
Out of envy, Joseph s brothers sold him into slavery.

00:16:44.600 --> 00:16:47.600
And this was by no means a minor offense.

00:16:47.600 --> 00:16:50.600
It began with Joseph being led to Egypt.

00:16:50.600 --> 00:16:54.600
Sometime later, he was falsely accused and thrown into prison.

00:16:54.600 --> 00:17:03.600
So for 13 years, Joseph suffered his treatment when he had done nothing to deserve it.

00:17:03.600 --> 00:17:09.599
Now it could have been very easy for Joseph to feel that if he ever saw his brothers again,

00:17:09.599 --> 00:17:15.599
the best option for peace would be not to have any dealings with them at all.

00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:18.599
Perhaps we might feel the same way as well.

00:17:18.599 --> 00:17:21.599
But Joseph didn t do that.

00:17:21.599 --> 00:17:27.599
In fact, after some years passed, both Joseph and his brothers sold peace.

00:17:27.599 --> 00:17:29.599
Now note how this was done.

00:17:29.599 --> 00:17:40.609
Turn with me please to the 105th Psalm and note the 19th verse of Psalm 105.

00:17:40.609 --> 00:17:47.650
It says, until the time that his word proved true,

00:17:47.650 --> 00:17:52.650
the saying of Jehovah is what refined him.

00:17:52.650 --> 00:18:02.279
Joseph trusted in Jehovah to refine him, to shape his thinking and godly qualities.

00:18:02.279 --> 00:18:05.279
He refused to become bitter.

00:18:05.279 --> 00:18:10.279
In fact, how interesting it is to note that there is nothing in the scriptures to indicate

00:18:10.279 --> 00:18:15.279
that Joseph ever told anyone, not even Pharaoh,

00:18:15.279 --> 00:18:21.279
that his brothers were the ones who kidnapped him and sold him as a slave.

00:18:22.279 --> 00:18:24.279
And how about Joseph s brothers?

00:18:24.279 --> 00:18:28.279
Years after they had mistreated him, they met Joseph in Egypt.

00:18:28.279 --> 00:18:33.279
When Joseph tested them by giving the youngest brother Benjamin significantly more attention

00:18:33.279 --> 00:18:38.279
than he gave the others, he saw his brothers had changed.

00:18:38.279 --> 00:18:42.279
They had let go of envy.

00:18:42.279 --> 00:18:47.279
They showed genuine concern for their brother and for their father Jacob.

00:18:47.279 --> 00:18:53.279
Joseph realized that his brothers were repentant and he forgave them.

00:18:53.279 --> 00:18:58.279
And because Joseph and his brothers were willing to take steps to sow peace,

00:18:58.279 --> 00:19:06.279
they reaped the benefits and eventually were able to enjoy a harmonious relationship.

00:19:06.279 --> 00:19:13.069
Well, how can the example of Joseph and his brothers help us today?

00:19:13.069 --> 00:19:26.500
In the following dramatization, notice how a family member sows peace.

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:39.200
Every morning, and I mean every morning, there's Jeremy singing at the top of his lungs.

00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:41.200
Okay, I wasn't the only one.

00:19:41.200 --> 00:19:43.200
No, but you were the loudest.

00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:46.200
Spoken like a true big brother.

00:19:46.200 --> 00:19:51.200
I was always impressed with how close you two were.

00:19:52.200 --> 00:19:56.200
Well, it wasn't always that way.

00:19:56.200 --> 00:19:58.200
No.

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:01.200
I mean, it started out that way.

00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:04.200
Nick and I, we weren't just brothers.

00:20:04.200 --> 00:20:07.670
We were friends.

00:20:07.670 --> 00:20:10.670
But then the family business ran into trouble.

00:20:10.670 --> 00:20:17.500
And what started as a small disagreement just exploded.

00:20:17.500 --> 00:20:19.500
How are business works?

00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:22.500
Instead of criticizing, could you just once?

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:26.779
Jeremy!

00:20:26.779 --> 00:20:29.779
Do you have any idea what this is going to cost us?

00:20:29.779 --> 00:20:31.779
I didn't have a choice. You went behind my back.

00:20:31.779 --> 00:20:34.779
What's your problem?

00:20:34.779 --> 00:20:36.779
You, you're the problem.

00:20:36.779 --> 00:20:50.579
We tried to work it out.

00:20:50.579 --> 00:20:55.460
But things just got worse.

00:20:55.460 --> 00:20:58.460
It was like a door slam shut between us.

00:20:58.460 --> 00:21:01.460
On the outside, I acted like everything was fine.

00:21:01.460 --> 00:21:14.230
But inside, I couldn't let it go.

00:21:14.230 --> 00:21:40.410
I felt like a total hypocrite and that had to change.

00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:46.410
I needed a lot of help from Jehovah to let go,

00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:56.359
to move on and make things right with Nick.

00:21:56.359 --> 00:22:01.109
It took a long time for the wounds to heal.

00:22:01.109 --> 00:22:11.670
And for us to trust each other, the way we used to.

00:22:11.670 --> 00:22:20.450
But we did.

00:22:20.450 --> 00:22:33.960
I'm so grateful that we made peace before the world turned upside down.

00:22:33.960 --> 00:22:37.960
So how can you and I imitate Joseph and his brothers?

00:22:37.960 --> 00:22:40.960
Let's discuss three steps.

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:46.960
The first step is found in Ephesians chapter 4, verse 32.

00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:48.960
Let's read that.

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:52.960
Ephesians 4, verse 32.

00:22:52.960 --> 00:23:00.099
But become kind to one another, tenderly compassionate,

00:23:00.099 --> 00:23:04.099
freely forgiving one another, just as God also by Christ,

00:23:04.099 --> 00:23:08.099
freely forgave you.

00:23:08.099 --> 00:23:13.099
So first, we must be ready to forgive.

00:23:13.099 --> 00:23:18.099
If we like grievances and resentment build up and develop in our hearts,

00:23:18.099 --> 00:23:22.099
it becomes even more difficult to be forgiving.

00:23:22.099 --> 00:23:26.099
Did you note in the video what started as a small disagreement

00:23:26.099 --> 00:23:31.099
between Nick and Jeremy exploded into something much bigger?

00:23:31.099 --> 00:23:33.099
Why?

00:23:33.099 --> 00:23:39.099
Jeremy could not let go of his resentment towards his brother.

00:23:39.099 --> 00:23:42.099
We must work to treat others in a forgiving way,

00:23:42.099 --> 00:23:45.099
just as Jehovah treats us.

00:23:46.509 --> 00:23:52.509
The second step, don't dwell on the offense.

00:23:52.509 --> 00:23:54.509
Proverbs 17 and 9 says,

00:23:54.509 --> 00:23:59.509
the one who keeps harping on a matter separates close friends.

00:23:59.509 --> 00:24:03.509
And isn't that how Jeremy described the relationship with his brother?

00:24:03.509 --> 00:24:07.509
It was a door slam shut between them.

00:24:07.509 --> 00:24:10.509
It wasn't until steps were taken to so peace,

00:24:10.509 --> 00:24:14.509
having that open, honest communication with each other,

00:24:14.509 --> 00:24:17.509
spending time together, working with each other in the ministry.

00:24:17.509 --> 00:24:22.509
Only then did things start to improve.

00:24:22.509 --> 00:24:24.509
And did you notice?

00:24:24.509 --> 00:24:28.509
Everything did not go back to normal right away.

00:24:28.509 --> 00:24:32.509
It took time to read peace.

00:24:32.509 --> 00:24:35.509
Time for those wounds to heal.

00:24:35.509 --> 00:24:38.509
Time to regain lost trust,

00:24:39.920 --> 00:24:42.920
so we can't look for miracles.

00:24:42.920 --> 00:24:46.920
But we should look for progress.

00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:49.920
Like the farmer, trust that.

00:24:49.920 --> 00:24:54.920
In new time, we will see results from our efforts.

00:24:54.920 --> 00:25:00.549
And here's where the all-important third step comes in.

00:25:00.549 --> 00:25:06.549
Ask Jehovah in prayer to help us to let go of resentment.

00:25:06.549 --> 00:25:09.549
Remember Psalm 105, 19?

00:25:09.549 --> 00:25:13.549
It was the sayings of Jehovah that helped refine Joseph

00:25:13.549 --> 00:25:16.549
to develop the qualities needed not to become bitter

00:25:16.549 --> 00:25:19.549
and to let go of any resentment.

00:25:19.549 --> 00:25:24.549
In the video, Jeremy acknowledged that he needed Jehovah's help,

00:25:24.549 --> 00:25:28.549
to let go and to move on.

00:25:28.549 --> 00:25:33.119
And Jehovah can do the same for us.

00:25:33.119 --> 00:25:35.119
It's not easy when we go through situations

00:25:35.119 --> 00:25:38.119
that threaten the peace of our family.

00:25:38.119 --> 00:25:41.119
But if we live by this fundamental principle,

00:25:41.119 --> 00:25:44.119
we reap what we sow.

00:25:44.119 --> 00:25:47.119
Then we can be assured that with the forgiving spirit,

00:25:47.119 --> 00:25:50.119
looking for opportunities to sow peace,

00:25:50.119 --> 00:25:53.119
and be seeking Jehovah for his help,

00:25:53.119 --> 00:25:55.119
that our efforts will be blessed.

00:25:55.119 --> 00:25:57.119
And in due time,

00:25:57.119 --> 00:26:00.119
we and our family can reap the benefits

00:26:00.119 --> 00:26:04.430
and enjoy true peace.

