it can be difficult at times to accept

00:27:17.140 --> 00:27:20.140
and then follow Jehovah's direction,

00:27:20.140 --> 00:27:24.140
or direction that we may receive from his organization,

00:27:24.140 --> 00:27:27.140
especially if we don't understand the reasons

00:27:27.140 --> 00:27:29.140
behind the direction,

00:27:29.140 --> 00:27:32.140
or it's not what we might prefer.

00:27:32.140 --> 00:27:36.140
What is needed to sow and reap peace?

00:27:36.140 --> 00:27:38.140
Humility.

00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:41.140
Humility is defined as a lowliness of mind,

00:27:41.140 --> 00:27:44.140
freedom from pride or arrogance.

00:27:44.140 --> 00:27:47.140
A humble person is not self-willed,

00:27:47.140 --> 00:27:50.140
but they actively look for ways to sow peace

00:27:50.140 --> 00:27:53.140
with Jehovah and others.

00:27:53.140 --> 00:27:56.140
He's known as a peacemaker.

00:27:56.140 --> 00:28:01.140
What is the result of humility and sowing peace?

00:28:01.140 --> 00:28:05.140
Notice what Proverbs 22 in verse 4 says.

00:28:05.140 --> 00:28:09.140
The result of humility and the fear of Jehovah is

00:28:09.140 --> 00:28:14.140
reaping notice riches and glory and life.

00:28:14.140 --> 00:28:17.140
Yes, everlasting life.

00:28:17.140 --> 00:28:20.140
The Bible contains many fine examples

00:28:20.140 --> 00:28:22.140
of those who sowed and reaped peace

00:28:22.140 --> 00:28:26.140
by humbly submitting to Jehovah's will.

00:28:26.140 --> 00:28:29.140
Let's consider the example of the Ghibbia Knights.

00:28:29.140 --> 00:28:32.140
The Ghibbia Knights weren't they enemies

00:28:32.140 --> 00:28:34.140
of the Israelites?

00:28:34.140 --> 00:28:35.140
Yes.

00:28:35.140 --> 00:28:38.140
So how did they humbly sow and reap peace with Jehovah

00:28:38.140 --> 00:28:41.140
and with his people?

00:28:41.140 --> 00:28:44.140
As you recall, after Joshua led the Israelites

00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:47.140
across the Jordan River into the Promised Land,

00:28:47.140 --> 00:28:49.140
Jehovah directed them to remove

00:28:49.140 --> 00:28:52.140
the pagan Canaanite nations who dwelt there.

00:28:52.140 --> 00:28:56.140
This included the Ghibbia Knights.

00:28:56.140 --> 00:28:59.140
The account that Joshua 9 informs us

00:28:59.140 --> 00:29:02.140
that the Ghibbia Knights were plainly told

00:29:02.140 --> 00:29:05.140
that it was Jehovah's will that the Canaanites

00:29:05.140 --> 00:29:07.140
be annihilated.

00:29:07.140 --> 00:29:11.140
Israel's stunning victories over Jericho and AI

00:29:11.140 --> 00:29:15.140
made it very clear that Jehovah was fighting for his people.

00:29:15.140 --> 00:29:18.140
And the Ghibbia Knights did not want to be next.

00:29:18.140 --> 00:29:23.140
But what could they do if this was Jehovah's will?

00:29:23.140 --> 00:29:26.140
Well, they devised an interesting plan.

00:29:26.140 --> 00:29:28.140
They sent representatives to seek peace

00:29:28.140 --> 00:29:32.140
with the Israelites and thereby with Jehovah.

00:29:32.140 --> 00:29:34.140
According to verse 11,

00:29:34.140 --> 00:29:37.579
they were instructed,

00:29:37.579 --> 00:29:39.579
we will be your servants.

00:29:39.579 --> 00:29:42.579
Now make a covenant with us.

00:29:42.579 --> 00:29:45.579
So this is what they were to say as representatives.

00:29:45.579 --> 00:29:49.579
Verse 4 says that the Ghibbia Knights acted shrewdly

00:29:49.579 --> 00:29:51.579
by trying to trick the Israelites

00:29:51.579 --> 00:29:54.579
with their worn out clothing and provisions,

00:29:54.579 --> 00:29:56.579
pretending that they had traveled

00:29:56.579 --> 00:29:58.579
from a very distant land,

00:29:58.579 --> 00:30:01.579
but were actually just 20 miles away.

00:30:01.579 --> 00:30:03.579
Did their plan work?

00:30:03.579 --> 00:30:06.579
Despite their deception, yes,

00:30:06.579 --> 00:30:08.579
their plan was successful.

00:30:08.579 --> 00:30:10.579
In fact, in verse 15,

00:30:10.579 --> 00:30:14.579
Joshua made a covenant of peace with the Ghibbia Knights.

00:30:14.579 --> 00:30:18.579
Evidently, this was in harmony with Jehovah's will

00:30:18.579 --> 00:30:21.579
and reflected their humility and desire

00:30:21.579 --> 00:30:24.579
to seek peace with him and his people.

00:30:24.579 --> 00:30:27.579
They demonstrated their humility and submission

00:30:27.579 --> 00:30:31.579
to Jehovah's will and his representative, Joshua,

00:30:31.579 --> 00:30:35.579
by following whatever direction they received.

00:30:35.579 --> 00:30:38.579
In fact, notice the direction in verse 27.

00:30:38.579 --> 00:30:41.579
It says, Joshua made them gatherers of wood

00:30:41.579 --> 00:30:44.579
and drawers of water for the assembly

00:30:44.579 --> 00:30:47.579
and for Jehovah's altar.

00:30:47.579 --> 00:30:51.579
Although the Ghibbia Knight men were likely skilled warriors,

00:30:51.579 --> 00:30:53.579
they were happy and content

00:30:53.579 --> 00:30:56.579
to do whatever work they were given

00:30:56.579 --> 00:30:58.579
to support pure worship.

00:30:58.579 --> 00:31:02.579
Humbly following direction saved their lives

00:31:02.579 --> 00:31:05.579
and brought them peace.

00:31:05.579 --> 00:31:09.579
How can we imitate the Ghibbia Knights?

00:31:09.579 --> 00:31:13.579
By bringing our lives into harmony with Jehovah's will.

00:31:14.579 --> 00:31:17.579
For some, this may require making big changes,

00:31:17.579 --> 00:31:19.579
adjusting their thinking,

00:31:19.579 --> 00:31:21.579
giving up harmful practices

00:31:21.579 --> 00:31:24.579
and avoiding bad associates.

00:31:24.579 --> 00:31:27.579
We can also imitate the Ghibbia Knights by being willing

00:31:27.579 --> 00:31:31.579
to perform whatever assignments we are given,

00:31:31.579 --> 00:31:34.579
humbly to support pure worship.

00:31:34.579 --> 00:31:36.579
So the lesson is clear.

00:31:36.579 --> 00:31:42.579
